üìò Experiment ‚Äì 10 : Install and Explore Selenium for Automated Testing
AIM

To install Selenium and explore its environment for automating web application testing.


Exp-10

OBJECTIVE

Install Selenium

Install WebDriver (ChromeDriver)

Write a Python script to automate Google search

Understand Selenium WebDriver workflow


Exp-10

SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS

Python installed

Selenium library

Chrome browser

ChromeDriver

Code editor (VS Code recommended)


Exp-10

üöÄ LAB PROCEDURE
1. Install Python

Download and install Python from:
https://www.python.org/downloads/

Verify installation:

python --version


Exp-10

2. Install Selenium Library

Install using pip:

pip install selenium


Exp-10

3. Download ChromeDriver
Step A ‚Äî Search for ChromeDriver

Search in Google: chrome driver for selenium
Then open the first link (as shown on page 2).


Exp-10

Step B ‚Äî Check Chrome version

Open:

chrome://settings/help


Match the Chrome version with the ChromeDriver version.
(Page 2 screenshot shows version checking.)


Exp-10

Step C ‚Äî Select Chrome for Testing Dashboard

Open the Chrome for Testing (CfT) availability dashboard.
Choose Stable version (page 3).


Exp-10

Step D ‚Äî Download ChromeDriver

Select your OS (Windows/macOS/Linux) and download the ZIP file.
(PDF page 4 shows all OS download options.)


Exp-10

Step E ‚Äî Extract & Set PATH

Extract ZIP file

Copy chromedriver.exe

Add its folder path to System Environment Variables ‚Üí PATH


Exp-10

4. Verify ChromeDriver Installation

Run:

chromedriver --version


Exp-10

5. Write Selenium Automation Script

Open VS Code ‚Üí Create test.py and paste the following code (from PDF page 5):

from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.service import Service
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys
import time

# Specify the correct path to your ChromeDriver
chrome_service = Service("C:\\Program Files\\chromedriver-win64\\chromedriver.exe")

# Set up the WebDriver for Chrome
driver = webdriver.Chrome(service=chrome_service)

try:
    # Step 1: Open Google in the browser
    driver.get("https://www.google.com")

    # Step 2: Locate the search box using the name attribute
    search_box = driver.find_element(By.NAME, "q")

    # Step 3: Enter the search term and press Enter
    search_box.send_keys("https://cmrcet.ac.in/")
    search_box.send_keys(Keys.RETURN)

    # Optional: Wait for a few seconds to see the search results
    time.sleep(20)

finally:
    # Step 4: Close the browser
    driver.quit()


‚ö†Ô∏è Important: Update the ChromeDriver path to match your system.


Exp-10

6. Run the Script

Execute:

python test.py


Browser will open and automatically search for cmrcet.ac.in on Google.


